Twitter tries to be more interesting for new users
The microblogging service Twitter has changed the process of registering users in order to quickly involve new participants in active interaction with the platform.
This measure should reduce the number of people who abandoned their microblogs.
Now new Twitter users will view a large number of accounts recommended by the service during registration to immediately make up their reading circle.
Recommendations are drawn up on the basis of the interests indicated in the registration.
In this case, Twitter automatically sets a check mark for all automatically selected accounts.
Because of this, the user will have to manually remove ticks in order not to read those who are not interested in him.
If earlier users of the microblogging service saw only avatars of recommended users, now Twitter displays a sample of one of the popular blogger’s tweets to help make an impression about a person.
This is the biggest change to Twitter’s registration page in three years.
Recently, Twitter is actively working on the modernization of the service.
Such activity is primarily associated with the continued attempts of the service to achieve break-even.
In 2014, the microblogging service faced a slowdown in user base growth and a drop in reader activity.
The company at the moment desperately needs more loyal resource of consumers who, once entered, would stay for a long time.
This is the only way to ensure a stable flow of advertising.
