The main problem of the “City of Sins-2” is different.
Frank Miller was good because as a draftsman he skillfully combined comics and noir, and as a director - turned the idea of how to transfer comics to the screen.
The comic and the noir are two aggressively opposed "realitys."
The phenomenon of comics in its modern form was born in the late 1920s, the same time when Dashiell Hammett's novels Bloody Harvest (1929), The Maltese Falcon (1930) and The Glass Key (1931) created the canon of noir, then called hard-boiled school - "cool school".
Pulp fiction.
