But in any movie based on comics, there was something flawed: the drawn characters stubbornly did not want to become screen flesh, remained pretenders in the “real” world around them.
Simply put, they were completely devoid of “existence”.
Noir, on the contrary, is the most existential genre of world literature.
After the world wars, the traditional novel - with experiences, characters, family scandals and historical background - lost all credibility.
What Forsythes, what Thibaults and Rugon-Maccars, what even Bolkonskys and Rostovs are generally conceivable after Verdun, Auschwitz and Hiroshima?
Such a novel peacefully mutated into a soap opera format, and the criminal - that is, by definition marginal - novel rose to the level of philosophical prose.
Hammett learned what it means to work as a paramedic at the front.
He was a communist.
As, by the way, were, at least, close to the Communist Party and such pillars of the genre as writers Horace McCoy and Jim Thompson, directors Jules Dassen, Joseph Lowsey, Edward Dmitrik.
Therefore, the noir, the archetype of which they set, is, firstly, rude and cynical, and secondly, purely social.
This is not the American version of social realism.
The first “Sin City” was remarkable precisely because it was unnatural, but organically connected the comic with the noir.
For the first time on the screen, the comic revived, not shy of its graphic nature, and did not pretend to be a “real” film.
The darkness of the corrupt world, where the cardinal ordered murders, and the senator covered the monstrous sadistic son, was quite worthy of Hammett’s pen.
And picturesque details like severed heads, with which the sadist decorated his nest, the pen of the genius James Ellroy, the author of the Black Orchid and the best - that is, declaratively nauseating - representative of the neonoir.
Sin City 2 is not even a retreat, but the capitulation of Miller-Rodrigues’ radical style to the comic book tradition.
This is largely due to 3D technology.
When you watch the second “Sin City”, you feel trapped in a glass ball, inside of which snow falls a toy cloaca.
However, most often it is not snow, but bloody mist, but by and large what’s the difference?
There is nothing to say about sociality.
After all, it is possible only when somewhere, somewhere we sometimes have, albeit on the side of a dirty swamp, but there is a normal world where you can return a girl who walked on a crooked path or, say, tell inconsolable parents that her destroyer is punished.
When there is no place for sin in the city, there is no sin but the norm.
Boring, like any norm.
The chaos of Sin City 2 is just boring.
In fairness, for the sake of domestic hire, he gave this unleavened sin a small, but a peppermint.
Titles warn: the film contains harmful scenes of smoking.
In relation to the spectacle, in the most vegetarian episode of which a person’s fingers are broken with forceps, this gives infernal humor.
